aphics, module grids, learning/assessment journey diagrams, carousel or tabs, premium CTA, responsive design, and subtle motion. No fake university partners, fake course catalogs, fake certifications, or fake metrics. Run lint/build.\"\n209 |   },\n210 |   {\n211 |     \"id\": \"26-platforms-industry-meshes\",\n212 |     \"title\": \"Design OREMesh RetailMesh TelecomVerse pages\",\n213 |     \"scope\": \"page-family-design\",\n214 |     \"target\": \"Platforms batch 4\",\n215 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n216 |     \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /platforms/oremesh, /platforms/retailmesh, and /platforms/telecomverse into premium industry platform product pages. Do not touch landing page. OREMesh should support mining/resource operations narrative. RetailMesh should support retail operations, customer experience, merchandising, store support, and executive visibility. TelecomVerse should support telecom operations, network support, customer experience, and field operations. Use industry-specific product hero visuals, mesh network diagrams, module carousels, agent cards, reference workflows, and related industry links. No fake clients, fake metrics, fake pricing, or fake deployments. Use Framer Motion/local CSS/SVG visuals. Run lint/build.\"\n217 |   },\n218 |   {\n219 |     \"id\": \"27-platforms-agent-runtime-developer\",\n220 |     \"title\": \"Design Agent Marketplace Runtime Governance Developer Platform\",\n221 |     \"scope\": \"page-family-design\",\n222 |     \"target\": \"Platforms batch 5\",\n223 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n224 |     \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /platforms/agent-marketplace, /platforms/runtime-governance, and /platforms/developer-platform. Do not touch landing page. Agent Marketplace should feel like a catalog of reusable enterprise agent patterns: knowledge agents, operations agents, compliance agents, customer experience agents, executive agents, document intelligence agents. Runtime Governance should focus on agent behavior, human oversight, permissions, monitoring, risk controls, auditability, and governance-first design without guaranteeing compliance. Developer Platform should feel like a developer-facing surface for building, testing, integrating, and operating enterprise agents, but no fake API keys or fake docs. Use product pages with tabs, carousels, technical diagrams, code-like visual blocks that are clearly illustrative, and strong CTAs. Run lint/build.\"\n225 |   },\n226 |   {\n227 |     \"id\": \"28-build-with-gff-pages\",\n228 |     \"title\": \"Design Build With GFF self-service tool pages\",\n229 |     \"scope\": \"page-family-design\",\n230 |     \"target\": \"Build pages\",\n231 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n232 |     \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /build and all Build With GFF subpages into polished self-service enterprise tool pages. Pages: /build, /build/talk, /build/blueprint, /build/assessment, /build/roi, /build/sandbox, /build/proposal, /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio. Do not touch landing page. Design mood: interactive, guided journey, conversion-focused, enterprise self-service. /build should show the journey: Visitor, AI Assessment, Blueprint, Workshop, Proposal, Contract, Delivery, Operate, Expand. /build/talk should feel like AI challenge intake with challenge description, industry, company size, frontend-only preview outputs Proposal, Squad, Timeline. /build/blueprint should be a polished wizard using the scoring rules. /build/assessment should feel like readiness diagnostic. /build/roi should feel like executive calculator with illustrative estimates only. /build/sandbox should feel like secure preview environment with no real runtime. /build/proposal should feel like proposal studio with PPT/PDF/SOW export cards as frontend preview only. /build/marketplace and /build/foundry-studio should be premium previews. Use forms, tabs, stepped flows, carousels, result panels, Framer Motion if available, Aceternity-inspired UI effects locally. No real API calls, no fake exports, no fake OTP. Run lint/build.\"\n233 |   },\n234 |   {\n235 |     \"id\": \"29-resources-pages\",\n236 |     \"title\": \"Design Resources and research library pages\",\n237 |     \"scope\": \"page-family-design\",\n238 |     \"target\": \"Resources pages\",\n239 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n240 |     \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /resources and all resource subpages into a premium research and intelligence library. Pages: /resources, /resources/blog, /resources/research, /resources/whitepapers, /resources/case-studies, /resources/architecture-library, /resources/videos, /resources/webinars, /resources/events, /resources/developer-docs, /resources/downloads, /resources/podcasts, /resources/reports, /resources/newsroom, /resources/patterns-of-intelligence, plus /insights and /insights/patterns-of-intelligence if present. Do not touch landing page. Design mood: editorial, research archive, thought leadership, intelligence library. Use featured research placeholder, category grids, resource carousels, architecture library visuals, report panels, newsletter CTA, filters using local state only if useful. Do not invent authors, dates, PDFs, downloads, report titles that imply real published assets, or fake media coverage. Use coming-soon states and category descriptions. Make every subpage feel intentionally designed but within the resource family. Run lint/build.\"\n241 |   },\n242 |   {\n243 |     \"id\": \"30-company-pages\",\n244 |     \"title\": \"Design Company pages\",\n245 |     \"scope\": \"page-family-design\",\n246 |     \"target\": \"Company pages\",\n247 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n248 |     \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /company and all company subpages into credible institutional pages. Pages: /company, /company/mission, /company/leadership, /company/locations, /company/partners, /company/advisors, /company/careers, /company/investors, /company/media, /company/contact. Do not touch landing page. Design mood: institutional, credible, global, leadership-driven. Include approved content: GFF AI PTE LTD., UEN 202621347N where appropriate, global AI strategy and deployment firm, Architects of the Agent Economy, founded and led by CEO Dr. Ashish Chandra, Singapore Global Headquarters, London Client Innovation Centre, India AI Engineering Factory, GFF AI Research Division, Garage Foundry Factory operating model. Locations page must show Singapore, London, India without inventing addresses. Leadership page may show Dr. Ashish Chandra where approved and placeholders for other leadership/advisors, no invented profiles. Partners/advisors/careers/investors/media should be polished pathways without fake names, fake job openings, fake partners, or fake press. Use global hub maps, institutional cards, narrative sections, carousels/tabs, premium CTAs, motion. Run lint/build.\"\n249 |   },\n250 |   {\n251 |     \"id\": \"31-contact-portal-client-control-center\",\n252 |     \"title\": \"Design Contact Portal Client Control Center pages\",\n253 |     \"scope\": \"utility-page-design\",\n254 |     \"target\": \"Contact Portal Client pages\",\n255 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n256 |     \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /contact, /portal, /portal/control-center, /client, and /client/control-center into premium secure enterprise utility pages. Do not touch landing page. Contact must show pathways: Talk To Sales, Book Workshop, Book Consultation, Sales, Support, Partnership, Media, University, Investors, Become Partner, Careers. Contact forms are frontend-only and must not call APIs. Portal must be a secure client workspace preview with login UI placeholder and modules: Dashboard, Projects, Programs, Documents, Invoices, Billing, Approvals, Support, Analytics, Governance, AI Operations, Control Center. Control Center must show preview modules: Agent Health, Delivery, Spend, Adoption, Governance without fake metrics or real data. Use secure product UI, clean forms, dashboard preview panels without fake numbers, subtle motion, mobile excellent. No auth, no backend, no fake data. Run lint/build.\"\n257 |   },\n258 |   {\n259 |     \"id\": \"32-legal-investor-pages\",\n260 |     \"title\": \"Design Legal Investor NDA privacy terms pages\",\n261 |     \"scope\": \"utility-page-design\",\n262 |     \"target\": \"Legal and investor pages\",\n263 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n264 |     \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /privacy, /terms, /nda, and /investor-relations into clean premium public utility pages. Do not touch landing page. These pages should be readable, institutional, and aligned with the site theme. Do not invent legal text that pretends to be final counsel-approved policy. Use clear placeholder copy where final legal language is required. Investor Relations should be a credible pathway page, not fake financial information. NDA page should explain how NDA requests will be handled later, not generate real legal documents. Use refined typography, structured sections, simple graphics, and CTA to contact. Run lint/build.\"\n265 |   },\n266 |   {\n267 |     \"id\": \"33-mobile-responsive-pass\",\n268 |     \"title\": \"Mobile responsive polish across all pages\",\n269 |     \"scope\": \"responsive-qa\",\n270 |     \"target\": \"all public pages\",\n271 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n272 |     \"prompt\": \"Perform a mobile responsive polish pass across landing and all public pages. Do not redesign. Fix only layout issues. Check hero, Quick Search, all homepage sections, Why GFF AI, Capabilities, Industries, Platforms, Build, Resources, Company, Contact, Portal, Client, Legal pages. Ensure no horizontal overflow, good section spacing, readable text, tappable buttons, stacked cards, simplified timelines, usable forms, scrollable tabs where needed, and architecture diagrams that adapt to mobile. Preserve approved landing visual design and hero video placement. Do not add new features. Run lint/build.\"\n273 |   },\n274 |   {\n275 |     \"id\": \"34-accessibility-and-motion-pass\",\n276 |     \"title\": \"Accessibility and motion quality pass\",\n277 |     \"scope\": \"accessibility-qa\",\n278 |     \"target\": \"all public pages\",\n279 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n280 |     \"prompt\": \"Perform accessibility and motion quality pass. Do not redesign. Ensure each public page has one clear H1, semantic sections, accessible links/buttons, visible focus states, form labels, keyboard-friendly interactions, no clickable divs without keyboard behavior, readable contrast, and prefers-reduced-motion support for animations. Check Command Center focus handling if present. Check carousels/tabs have accessible controls. Keep animations subtle and premium. Do not remove approved landing animations unless broken. Run lint/build.\"\n281 |   },\n282 |   {\n283 |     \"id\": \"35-visual-premium-polish-pass\",\n284 |     \"title\": \"Premium UI polish pass\",\n285 |     \"scope\": \"visual-polish\",\n286 |     \"target\": \"all public pages except approved hero\",\n287 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n288 |     \"prompt\": \"Perform a final premium UI polish pass. Do not redesign the approved landing hero or move its video. Improve visual quality only where the implementation looks generic, unfinished, boxy, or cheap. Target all new public pages and new homepage sections. Make the UI feel like a custom expensive 2026 enterprise AI website: refined spacing, strong hierarchy, clean cards, thoughtful graphics, carousels/tabs where useful, SVG architecture visuals, subtle gradients, balanced motion, no excessive pills or badges, no box-inside-box clutter. Do not add fake data or content. Do not add dependencies. Do not change global styles in a way that breaks landing. Run lint/build.\"\n289 |   },\n290 |   {\n291 |     \"id\": \"36-link-route-content-audit\",\n292 |     \"title\": \"Route link and content audit\",\n293 |     \"scope\": \"audit-fix\",\n294 |     \"target\": \"all links and content\",\n295 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n296 |     \"prompt\": \"Audit all nav, footer, homepage section, CTA, related-link, card, carousel, tab, and form links. Fix broken or incorrect links only. Ensure all public pages are explicit. Ensure no href points to removed slug/catch-all paths. Check that required public routes exist: top-level, Why GFF AI, Capabilities, Industries, Platforms, Build, Resources, Company, Contact, Portal, Client, Insights, Privacy, Terms, NDA, Investor Relations. Ensure content includes GFF AI positioning, Garage Foundry Factory, global footprint, research/IP where appropriate, and no fake data. Run lint/build.\"\n297 |   },\n298 |   {\n299 |     \"id\": \"37-final-full-build-and-qa\",\n300 |     \"title\": \"Final full Phase 0-2 QA\",\n301 |     \"scope\": \"final-qa\",\n302 |     \"target\": \"whole project\",\n303 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n304 |     \"prompt\": \"Perform final QA for the complete Phase 0 to Phase 2 build. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify landing page has approved hero preserved, hero video placement unchanged, hero copy and metrics correct, Enterprise Quick Search present and local, Garage Foundry Factory journey present, What We Build present, Interactive Experience present, Global Presence present, Client Success present, Live Dashboard present without fake numbers, Latest Research present, Footer complete. Verify explicit routes exist and no slug logic or PublicRoutePage exists. Verify all public pages have premium unique UI, category design families, mobile responsiveness, accessibility basics, no fake data, no backend/API/AWS/auth/OTP/export behavior. Verify Blueprint banking test returns 87/100. Run npm run lint and npm run build if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed in final QA, commands run, remaining warnings, and any remaining TODOs.\"\n305 |   },\n306 |   {\n307 |     \"id\": \"38-phase3-preflight-interactive-tools-audit\",\n308 |     \"title\": \"Phase 3 preflight audit for interactive Build With GFF tools\",\n309 |     \"scope\": \"phase3-audit\",\n310 |     \"target\": \"Build With GFF interactive product layer\",\n311 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n\n[Showing lines 1-311 of 1170. Use start_line/end_line to read other sections.]","success":true}],"durationMs":5}}
