ame`, and so on. Also, the `AgentOperation` model is next on my list to check for requirements.\n\n\n\n**Verifying Data Model Consistency**\n\nI'm now meticulously reviewing and verifying the fields in `AgentOperation` and `DocumentItem` models. I've confirmed `AgentOperation` includes `project_id`, `agent_type`, `status`, and `health`, with relationships. The plan is to continue confirming database consistency to ensure `DocumentItem`'s `client_id`, `project_id`, `title`, and `document_type` are correct.\n\n\n**Analyzing Invoice Fields**\n\nI'm now analyzing the `Invoice` fields, checking the data types for `amount` and `currency`. I'm verifying data model consistency, especially the `amount` field, to align with the Phase 4 UI requirements. The goal is to accurately define each field's type. Specifically, I need to choose between `Integer`, `Float`, or a `Numeric` for the `amount` and `currency` fields.\n\n\n**Defining Invoice Fields**\n\nI've set the `amount` field in the `Invoice` model as `Column(Float)` for flexibility, and I'm adding `invoice_number`, `status`, `due_date`, and `issued_date`. I've started defining the `SupportTicket` model now, with fields such as `client_id`, `project_id`, `title`, and `category`. I'm verifying the new schema!\n\n\n**Defining GovernanceItem Relationships**\n\nI'm now integrating the `GovernanceItem` model, defining its fields and relationships. I'm focusing on ensuring data integrity with precise data types and foreign key constraints. The plan is to create simple and clear relationships with the `ClientAccount` and `Project` models, and the code looks very clean and efficient.\n\n\n**Defining Relationships with Cascades**\n\nI'm now implementing cascading deletes with `cascade=\"all, delete-orphan\"` in the model relationships to prevent orphaned records. I've updated the `ClientAccount`, `Project`, and `AgentOperation` models with necessary relationships, establishing clear linkages to support data integrity and automatic deletion of associated data.\n\n\n"}}
