{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:01:03.260Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"gaadwpi3","input":{"summary":"I have successfully implemented all requested MVP core database models for the admin and client portals in GFF AI. No landing pages or GFF AI tools were modified, keeping the implementation purely modular.\n\n### Summary of Implementation:\n1. **User Model (`user.py`)**: Modified the existing `User` model to fully support `id`, `name`, `email`, `hashed_password`, `role` (supporting `client_admin`, `client_member`, and `gff_admin`), nullable `client_id` with foreign key, `status`, `created_at`, and `updated_at`. Preserved `full_name` and `is_active` for seamless backward compatibility with existing authorization code.\n2. **ClientAccount Model (`client_account.py`)**: Created this model with fields `id`, `name`, `industry`, `region`, `status`, `account_owner`, and `created_at`, linking as a parent to other entities.\n3. **Project Model (`project.py`)**: Created this model with fields `id`, `client_id`, `name`, `phase`, `status`, `health`, `owner`, `start_date`, `target_date`, `progress`, and `description`.\n4. **AgentOperation Model (`agent_operation.py`)**: Created this model with fields `id`, `client_id`, nullable `project_id`, `name`, `agent_type`, `status`, `health`, `owner`, `governance_status`, and `last_activity_at`.\n5. **DocumentItem Model (`document_item.py`)**: Created this model with fields `id`, `client_id`, nullable `project_id`, `title`, `document_type`, `status`, `version`, `owner`, `visibility`, and `created_at`.\n6. **Invoice Model (`invoice.py`)**: Created this model with fields `id`, `client_id`, nullable `project_id`, `invoice_number`, `status`, `amount` (as Float), `currency`, `due_date`, and `issued_date`.\n7. **SupportTicket Model (`support_ticket.py`)**: Created this model with fields `id`, `client_id`, nullable `project_id`, `title`, `category`, `priority`, `status`, `assigned_to`, `created_by`, `description`, and `created_at`.\n8. **GovernanceItem Model (`governance_item.py`)**: Created this model with fields `id`, `client_id`, nullable `project_id`, `title`, `severity`, `status`, `owner`, `due_date`, and `description`.\n\n### Relationships & Import Safety:\n- Implemented clean cascading and optional relationships among `ClientAccount`, `Project`, and other core database entities.\n- Registered all new models under `backend/app/models/__init__.py` and metadata mapping inside `backend/app/db/base.py`.\n- Deferring the base metadata import inside `init_db` perfectly resolved a circular import issue, allowing clean module-wide importing of any model.\n\n### Validation Done:\n- Successfully validated imports for individual models directly from `backend.app.models`.\n- Verified SQLAlchemy metadata registration: all 8 models correctly output on `Base.metadata.tables.keys()`.\n- Successfully ran the DB seeding script `backend/app/seed.py`, creating a clean SQLite database at `backend/dev.db` and populating initial seed users without errors.\n- Verified TypeScript compilation (`npx tsc --noEmit`) and project-wide ESLint linting successfully.","verified":true}}}
